			<p><b>Nagara Operational Timeline</b></p><table border='0' cellspacing='0'><tr bgcolor='eeeeee'><td valign='top' align='right' nowrap><a href='/event/today/04/21/1922' alt='See all events on 21 Apr 1922' title='See all events on 21 Apr 1922' class='noStyle'>21 Apr 1922</a>&nbsp;</td><td>Nagara was commissioned into service.</td></tr><tr bgcolor=''><td valign='top' align='right' nowrap><a href='/event/today/06/15/1942' alt='See all events on 15 Jun 1942' title='See all events on 15 Jun 1942' class='noStyle'>15 Jun 1942</a>&nbsp;</td><td>Nagara transferred 500 wounded survivors of the Battle of Midway to hospital ship Hikawa Maru.</td></tr></table><br /><p><b>Photographs</b></p><table cellpadding='2' cellspacing='0' border='0'><tr><td><a href="/image.php?image_id=7833"><img src="/images/imagemagick/tmb_ship_nagara2.jpg" border='0' alt='Light cruiser Nagara, date unknown'></a></td></tr></table><br /><p><b>Maps</b></p><table cellpadding='2' cellspacing='0' border='0'><tr><td><a href="/image.php?image_id=23505"><img src="/images/imagemagick/tmb_54e443b30cda3.jpg" border='0' alt='Map depicting Japanese and US Naval movements during the Second Naval Battle of Guadalcanal the night of Nov 14, 1942.'></a></td></tr></table><br /><br /><br /><br />
